# Knowledge base access control
#
# This file defines who must approve PRs for different parts of the repo.
# Combined with branch protection rules (require PR reviews before merging),
# this creates the two-tier access model described in README.md.
#
# How it works:
# - Files matched by a pattern below require review from the listed team/users
# - Files NOT matched here can be approved by any contributor with write access
# - Later patterns override earlier ones
#
# See ADMIN_SETUP.md for how to configure branch protection to make this effective.

# --- Admin-controlled files (require admin review) ---

# Repo-level configuration and documentation
/README.md                          @Entropic-Science/admins
/CODEOWNERS                         @Entropic-Science/admins
/ADMIN_SETUP.md                     @Entropic-Science/admins

# Active projects files — only updated through accepted proposals
/divisions/infrastructure/ACTIVE_PROJECTS.md    @Entropic-Science/admins
/divisions/research/ACTIVE_PROJECTS.md          @Entropic-Science/admins
/divisions/outreach-fundraising/ACTIVE_PROJECTS.md  @Entropic-Science/admins

# --- Community-editable files (any write-access contributor can approve) ---
# These are NOT listed here, which means any reviewer can approve PRs to them:
#   - /divisions/*/ROSTER.md
#   - /divisions/*/PROPOSALS.md
#   - /library/**
